    "title": "Keto Granola",
    "link": "/ketoGranola",
    "image": null,
    "date": "4 Nov, 2016",
    "category": ["breakfast"],
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://farm1.staticflickr.com/741/31328471570_693ee2da8e_o_d.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>This is my go-to keto breakfast with some coconut milk or greek yogurt, and it is also great when I am travelling (I just ask for some whole-fat yogurt and add my granola right there!). It is more of a guideline to make your own keto-fied granola, a low carb and extra crunchy cereal that you can customize to your own taste.</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>3/4 cup (105 g) of hemp hearts or seeds</li>\n  <li>1,5 cups of nuts of choice; I use 1 cup of almonds and 1/2 cup of hazelnuts</li>\n  <li>1/4 cup pepitas (30g)</li>\n  <li>1/3 cup cocoa nibs (40g)</li>\n  <li>4 tbsp (12 g) of chopped dried cranberries</li>\n  <li>1/4 tsp cinnamon</li>\n  <li>1/8 tsp salt</li>\n  <li>30 g extra virgin coconut oil</li>\n  <li>Sweetener to taste - 2-3 tbsp erythritol</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Process</strong>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Toast the nuts (unless you buy them toasted like i do).</li>\n      <li>Mix all the dry ingredients.</li>\n      <li>Mix the sweetener with the melted oil, than pour over the dry ingredients and mix well.</li>\n      <li>Let it set in the fridge. Then, take out and break it into smaller chunks.</li>\n      <li>Keep in the fridge until consumed. It lasts up to 2 weeks.</li>\n    </ol>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Nutritional info</strong>, <em>per serving (serves 9)</em>\n    <ul>\n      <li>287 kCal</li>\n      <li><strong>4.5 g net carbs</strong>, 4.1 g fiber, 8.6 g total carbs</li>\n      <li>Without cocoa nibs: 0.8 g net carbs less. Without the cranberries, 1 g net carbs less.</li>\n      <li>10.1 g protein</li>\n      <li>25.7 g fat</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
    "excerpt": "This is my go-to keto breakfast with some coconut milk or greek yogurt, and it is also great when I..."
