    "title": "Keto Chocolate",
    "link": "/ketoChocolate",
    "image": null,
    "date": "19 Oct, 2016",
    "category": ["snack"],
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://farm1.staticflickr.com/293/31676698135_795c1b0ace_o_d.jpg\" /></p>\n\n<p>This is a super easy recipe for no-sugar chocolate without any weird artificial sweeteners or additives :)</p>\n\n<ul>\n    <li>1/4 cup coconut oil or butter</li>\n    <li>1/4 peanut butter, almond butter, hazelnut butter, tahini...</li>\n    <li>A pinch of salt</li>\n    <li>1/3 cup cacao</li>\n    <li>Stevia or erythritol to taste</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Process</strong>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Melt the oil.</li>\n      <li>Mix all the ingredients. Taste to adjust sweetness.</li>\n      <li>Pour on a flat non-stick surface and put in the freezer until it hardens.</li>\n      <li>Divide into 9 pieces and keep in the fridge or freezer.</li>\n    </ol>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Nutritional info</strong>, <em>per portion (makes 9 portions)</em>\n    <ul>\n      <li>95 kCal</li>\n      <li>3.1 g total carbs, 1.6 g fiber, 1.5 g net carbs</li>\n      <li>2.5 g protein</li>\n      <li>9.2 g fat</li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
