    "title": "Chicken/paneer tikka",
    "link": "/tikkaEng",
    "image": null,
    "date": "11 Apr, 2016",
    "category": ["snack"],
    "content": "<p><img src=\"https://farm1.staticflickr.com/679/30857035844_7ab9ae46fa_o_d.jpg \" /></p>\n\n<p>Chicken tikka, that can also be made with paneer or tofu, is an easy to make appetizer, very versatile to add to other dishes, or to just eat it plain.</p>\n\n<p>I like to make it with big chunks of onion and red bell pepper, to have more color and different flavors.</p>\n\n<p>It is good as it is, in salad or sandwiches, and it is also the base for the typical dish Chicken Tikka Masala, one of the most popular foods at indian restaurants.</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>2 big chicken breasts (600g), cubed, or 500 g paneer or firm tofu, cubed</li>\n  <li>1/2 cup (125g) greek-style yoghurt. <i>Use vegan yoghurt and tofu for a vegan dish</i></li>\n  <li>Optional: 2 tbsp fresh coriander, chopped</li>\n  <li>1/2 tsp chili or to taste</li>\n  <li>1/4 tsp paprika</li>\n  <li>1 tsp salt</li>\n  <li>1 tbsp ginger paste, 1 tbsp garlic paste</li>\n  <li>1/4 tsp turmeric</li>\n  <li>Juice of half a lemon</li>\n  <li>Optional: 1/2 onion and 1/2 red bell pepper, in big chunks</li>\n</ul>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Process</strong>\n    <ol>\n      <li>Put all the ingredients in a bowl and marinate for at least 2 hours.</li>\n      <li>Put the meat, onion and pepper into skewers and on an oven tray. (if using wooden skewers, soak them in water for a couple of hours and then cover the part that doesn’t have meat with some aluminum foil).\n        <ul>\n          <li>Another option, instead of making it in the oven, is to make it in a pan over high heat with some oil, without skewers.</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li>Put under the grill for 20 min turning it every 5 and pouring some of the marination sauce on top if it dries out.</li>\n      <li>Once it starts getting slightly burnt in the corners, it is done.</li>\n      <li>Use for tikka masala, pizza, sandwiches, salad…</li>\n    </ol>\n  </li>\n  <li><strong>Nutritional info</strong>, per 1/5 recipe without vegetables\n    <ul>\n      <li>With chicken (1 chicken breast per serving):\n        <ul>\n          <li>162 kCal</li>\n          <li><strong>1.7 g net carbs</strong>, 0.1 g fiber</li>\n          <li>27.4 g protein</li>\n          <li>4.4 g fat</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li>With paneer (100 g paneer per serving):\n        <ul>\n          <li>327 kCal</li>\n          <li><strong>5 g net carbs</strong>, 0.1 g fiber</li>\n          <li>22.3 g protein</li>\n          <li>24.8 g fat</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n      <li>With firm tofu (100 g tofu per serving):\n        <ul>\n          <li>173 kCal</li>\n          <li><strong>3.7 g net carbs</strong>, 2.4 g fiber</li>\n          <li>18.2 g protein</li>\n          <li>10.1 g fat</li>\n        </ul>\n      </li>\n    </ul>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n\n",
    "excerpt": "Chicken tikka, that can also be made with paneer or tofu, is an easy to make appetizer, very versatile to..."
